---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
import ToolCTA from "../../components/ToolCTA.astro";
---

<GuideLayout
  title="How to Calculate GPA with Credits"
  description="Learn how grade points, credits, and quality points work together in a GPA calculation."
  slug="/guides/how-to-calculate-gpa-with-credits"
  heroTitle="How to Calculate GPA with Credits"
  heroText="Use credits, grade points, and quality points to calculate term GPA and cumulative GPA."
>
  <div class="guide-body">
    <section class="card">
      <h2>GPA is credit-weighted</h2>
      <p>Courses with more credits affect your GPA more. A 4-credit course has twice the GPA impact of a 2-credit course.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Formula</h2>
      <p class="formula-block">GPA = Total quality points / Total credits</p>
      <p>Quality points are grade points multiplied by credits. A 3-credit class with an A earns 12 quality points on a 4.0 scale.</p>
    </section>

    <ToolCTA
      title="Calculate GPA by Credits"
      text="Use the GPA Calculator to enter courses, credits, and grades in letter, percentage, or point value format."
      links={[{ href: "/gpa-calculator/", label: "Use GPA Calculator" }]}
    />

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Common mistakes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Treating every class as equal even when credit values differ.</li>
        <li>Counting pass/fail, incomplete, or withdrawal grades when they do not affect GPA.</li>
        <li>Confusing weighted high school GPA with college GPA.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What are quality points?</h3><p>Quality points are grade points multiplied by course credits.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Do P or W grades count?</h3><p>Usually they are ignored for GPA, though your school policy is the final source.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I include prior GPA?</h3><p>Yes. The GPA Calculator can combine prior GPA and completed credits with current coursework.</p></div>
    </section>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>
